 Palestinians, separated from family members and their homeland. This is the second book in the Women’s Voices from Gaza series, which honours women’s unique and underrepresented perspectives on the social, material, and political realities of Palestinian life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aWomen political activistszGaza StripzGazavBiography. 0aWomen, Palestinian ArabzGaza StripzGazavBiography. 0aWomen, Palestinian ArabzGaza StripzGazaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aWomen, Palestinian ArabzGaza Strip. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Women.2bisacsh  aIsrael.  aNakba.  acatastrophe of dispossession.  acollective memories.  aculture.  aexile.  agender.  agenerational experience.  ahistoriography.  ahistory from below.  ahuman rights.  anon-fiction.  aoral history.  atraditional historical narrative.  awomen.  awomen’s studies.1 aAgeel, Ghada, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBaroud, Ramzy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBill, Barbara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212570240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772125702423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772125702/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles